Sometimes, resource IDs doesn&#39;t regenerate properly on build. This happens mostly when we are trying to set a resource as an `int` value.

For example this `ContextCompat.getDrawable(mContext, R.drawable.your_image)` can cause `Resources$NotFoundException` on some phones so I had to catch it like below:

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    try {
      mImage.setImageDrawable(ContextCompat.getDrawable(mContext, R.drawable.your_image));
    } catch (Resources.NotFoundException e) {
      mImage.setImageResource(R.drawable.your_image);
    }

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt; 

Catching Exceptions isn&#39;t the answer obviously, this is a build problem and more investigations are needed to find the exact cause.

